VALUES
(42, 2, 39, 42, 2, 21, 24, 'performed all things according to the law of the Lord', 'Fulfillment of the Law', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of performing all things according to the law of the Lord. The actions of Mary and Joseph in presenting Jesus and returning to Nazareth highlight their adherence to the law throughout Jesus'' early life.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 40, 42, 2, 52, 52, 'filled with wisdom', 'Growth and Favor of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' growth in wisdom and favor. The first mentions being ''filled with wisdom,'' while the second states he ''increased in wisdom and stature.''', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 40, 42, 1, 80, 80, 'waxed strong in spirit', 'Growth and Strength in Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the growth and strength of the child in spirit. They highlight a similar developmental theme, indicating a divine influence in their lives.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 40, 23, 11, 1, 5, 'filled with wisdom', 'Connection of Wisdom and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of the spirit of wisdom. Luke describes Jesus as ''filled with wisdom,'' while Isaiah speaks of the spirit of wisdom resting upon the coming Branch. This connection highlights the continuity of divine wisdom in the growth of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 40, 43, 1, 14, 14, 'the grace of God was upon him', 'Connection of Grace and Growth', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of grace. In Luke, the child is described as ''filled with wisdom'' and ''the grace of God was upon him,'' while in John, the Word is ''full of grace and truth.'' This connection highlights the significance of grace in the development and identity of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 40, 9, 2, 26, 26, 'the grace of God was upon him', 'Growth and Favor with God', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of a child who gains favor with God. Luke highlights Jesus being ''filled with wisdom'' and ''the grace of God was upon him,'' while Samuel is noted for being ''in favour both with the Lord.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 40, 9, 3, 19, 19, NULL, 'Growth and Divine Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of a young boy under divine favor. Luke highlights Jesus being ''filled with wisdom'' and ''the grace of God was upon him,'' while Samuel is noted for growing with ''the Lord was with him.''', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 40, 23, 53, 1, 2, 'grew, and waxed strong in spirit', 'Growth and Divine Favor', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of a significant figure. Luke describes the child growing strong in spirit, while Isaiah speaks of him growing as a tender plant, indicating a divine development.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 41, 2, 12, 14, 14, 'the feast of the passover', 'Connection of Annual Feast Observance', 'This connection highlights the importance of annual feasts in both passages. Luke 2:41 mentions the yearly pilgrimage to Jerusalem for Passover, while Exodus 12:14 establishes Passover as a perpetual feast.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 41, 2, 23, 14, 17, 'feast of the passover', 'Annual Pilgrimage to Jerusalem', 'This connection highlights the practice of attending annual feasts. Both passages emphasize the importance of observing religious festivals, with Luke noting the annual trip to Jerusalem for Passover, aligning with the command in Exodus for males to appear before the Lord during feasts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 41, 3, 23, 5, 5, 'feast of the passover', 'Connection of Passover Observance', 'This connection highlights the annual observance of Passover by Jesus'' parents in Luke, which aligns with the established timing of the Passover in Leviticus. Both passages emphasize the significance of this feast in the Jewish tradition.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 41, 4, 28, 16, 16, 'feast of the passover', 'Connection of Passover Observance', 'This connection highlights the annual observance of Passover by Jesus'' parents in Luke, which is rooted in the commandment given in Numbers regarding the timing of the Passover. Both passages emphasize the significance of the Passover as a key event in the Jewish calendar.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 41, 5, 12, 18, 18, 'feast of the passover', 'Annual Pilgrimage to Jerusalem', 'This connection highlights the importance of annual feasts in both passages. Luke 2:41 mentions the yearly pilgrimage to Jerusalem for Passover, while Deuteronomy 12:18 emphasizes rejoicing before the Lord during feasts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 41, 5, 16, 1, 8, 'feast of the passover', 'Passover Observance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of observing the Passover. Luke 2:41 mentions Jesus'' parents going to Jerusalem for the feast, reflecting the command in Deuteronomy 16:1-8 to keep the Passover unto the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 41, 9, 1, 3, 3, NULL, 'Annual Pilgrimage to Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the practice of yearly pilgrimage to worship God. In Luke, Jesus'' parents go to Jerusalem for Passover, while in 1 Samuel, the man goes to Shiloh to worship and sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 43, 2, 12, 15, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Obedience and Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of fulfilling obligations and the significance of presence. In Luke, Jesus remains in Jerusalem, indicating a deeper commitment, while Exodus emphasizes the importance of adhering to commands regarding unleavened bread.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 43, 14, 30, 21, 23, 'Jerusalem', 'Joyful Gathering in Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize a significant event in Jerusalem involving a gathering. In Luke, Jesus remains in Jerusalem, while in 2 Chronicles, the Israelites celebrate the feast with gladness in the same city.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 43, 14, 25, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Seeking and Encountering', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking and encountering. In both passages, there is an emphasis on individuals seeking to come together, whether it be Jesus remaining in Jerusalem or Amaziah reaching out to Joash.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 44, 19, 122, 1, 4, 'a day’s journey', 'Journey to Worship Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of a journey towards a sacred place. In Luke 2:44, the family undertakes a journey, while Psalms 122:1-4 expresses joy in going to the house of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 44, 23, 2, 3, 3, 'went a day’s journey', 'Journey to Seek Understanding', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking knowledge and guidance. In both passages, there is an emphasis on going forth to find wisdom and understanding, whether it is in the context of family or divine instruction.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 44, 19, 42, 4, 4, 'went a day’s journey', 'Journey and Community in Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the experience of being part of a community during a journey. In Luke, the family travels together, while in Psalms, the speaker recalls going with the multitude to worship. This connection highlights the importance of communal experiences in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 46, 23, 49, 1, 2, 'both hearing them, and asking them questions', 'Connection of Wisdom and Calling', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine calling and wisdom. In Luke, Jesus is found in the temple, engaging with learned individuals, while Isaiah speaks of being called from the womb and equipped with a sharp mouth, suggesting a profound wisdom and purpose.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 46, 42, 5, 17, 17, NULL, 'Teaching and Learning in the Temple', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus engaging with learned individuals. Both passages emphasize Jesus'' interaction with ''doctors'' and his role as a teacher.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 46, 23, 50, 4, 4, 'hearing them, and asking them questions', 'Wisdom and Learning in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of learning and understanding. Both passages emphasize the importance of being taught and hearing wisdom, as seen in Jesus'' engagement with the doctors and the Lord''s provision of a learned tongue.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 46, 44, 5, 34, 34, 'doctors', 'Connection of Learning and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of learning and authority in both passages. In Luke, Jesus is found ''in the temple, sitting in the midst of the doctors,'' while in Acts, Gamaliel is described as ''a doctor of the law,'' indicating a shared emphasis on scholarly discourse.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 46, 40, 12, 40, 40, 'three days', 'Three Days Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''three days'' in both passages. In Luke, Jesus is found after three days, while in Matthew, he refers to being three days and three nights in the heart of the earth.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 46, 40, 27, 63, 64, 'after three days', 'Connection of Three Days', 'This connection highlights the significance of ''three days'' in both passages. In Luke, Jesus is found in the temple after three days, while in Matthew, the mention of ''three days'' relates to the resurrection prediction.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 46, 11, 12, 5, 5, 'three days', 'Three Days of Waiting', 'This connection highlights the theme of waiting for three days in both passages. In Luke, the three days lead to the discovery of Jesus in the temple, while in 1 Kings, the three days signify a period of deliberation before the people return for a decision.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 47, 40, 7, 28, 28, 'astonished at his understanding', 'Astonishment at Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the astonishment of the listeners at Jesus'' understanding and doctrine. This connection highlights the impact of his teachings on those who heard him.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 47, 19, 119, 99, 99, 'astonished at his understanding', 'Understanding and Wisdom Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of understanding gained through meditation on divine teachings. In Luke, the astonishment at Jesus'' understanding parallels the psalmist''s claim of having more understanding than teachers due to meditating on God''s testimonies.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
